> He waits for his team to report back
>
> OOC: For your knowledge, it is a sphere of energon, of variable
> stability and buried at about 20 meters in the ground.
>

{Nightshade}

    "Nightshade terroize!" she spoke as she transformed, her fore arm
opening and sliding from within a small reader before moving to a spot where
Warhead indicated the energon to be. The reader whirred as she began
scanning the stability mapping out the crystalis and which would be the best
and worst spots to take a sample from. She frowned that the energon of this
random stability wasn't exposed to the surface, she could have placed a det
charge amongst the crystals and hjad it go off when Warhead was collecting
his sample...raw unstable energon was a convienent cover up for removing
certain bots.

    Smiling she  finished collecting the reading, reporting to Warhead the
safest crystal section to take a sample from towards the rear of the
cluster, it would most likely mean some digging though. To remove the
troublesome bot would come later, for now she'd work with him.
